### Description

I'm facing an issue with our custom Angular grid library where ng-content projection with e-columns directives is not working as expected. Specifically, the child directives are not being fetched correctly when using ng-content in a separate component. I have getting undefined value from the childColumns and it doesn’t query the directives values.

**Grid Component Source:**

**// grid.component.ts**

```import { ColumnsDirective } from './columns.directive';

@Component({
  selector: 'ejs-grid',
  inputs: inputs,
  outputs: outputs,
  template: '',
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
  queries: {
    childColumns: new ContentChild(ColumnsDirective),
  }
})
@ComponentMixins([ComponentBase])
export class GridComponent extends Grid implements IComponentBase {
  public childColumns: QueryList<ColumnsDirective>;
  public childAggregates: QueryList<AggregatesDirective>;

public ngAfterContentChecked(): void {
        this.tagObjects[0].instance = this.childColumns;
        this.context.ngAfterContentChecked(this);
    }
}

**// columns.directive.ts**

@Directive({
  selector: 'ejs-grid>e-columns>e-column',
  inputs: input,
  outputs: outputs,
  queries: {
    childColumns: new ContentChild(StackedColumnsDirective)
  }
})
export class ColumnDirective extends ComplexBase<ColumnDirective> {
  // properties
}

@Directive({
  selector: 'ejs-grid>e-columns',
  queries: {
    children: new ContentChildren(ColumnDirective)
  }
})
export class ColumnsDirective extends ArrayBase<ColumnsDirective> {

}
```

**Sample Code to Reproduce:**
```
// parent.component.ts

import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';
import { stringData } from './data'; // Assume data is imported from a data source
import { DataService } from './data.service';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-parent',
  template: `
    <app-reusable-grid [data]="data">
      <e-columns>
        <e-column field='OrderID' headerText='Order ID' textAlign='Right' width=90></e-column>
        <e-column field='EmployeeID' headerText='Employee ID' textAlign='Right' width=80></e-column>
        <e-column field='ShipCity' headerText='Ship City' width=100></e-column>
        <e-column field='ShipName' headerText='Ship Name' width=120 visible='false'></e-column>
      </e-columns>
    </app-reusable-grid>
  `
})
export class ParentComponent implements OnInit {
  public data?: any;
  
  constructor(private dataService: DataService) {}

  ngOnInit(): void {
    this.dataService.getData().subscribe({
      next: (response) => {
        this.data = response;
        console.log(this.data);
      },
      error: (err) => {
        console.error('Error fetching data', err);
      }
    });
  }
}

// reusable-grid.component.ts

import { Component, Input } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-reusable-grid',
  template: `
    <ejs-grid [dataSource]="data">
      <ng-content></ng-content>
    </ejs-grid>
  `
})
export class ReusableGridComponent {
  @Input() data?: any[];
}
```
**Issue:**

When using e-columns directives directly in the ejs-grid tag, the child directives are fetched correctly. However, when passing e-columns through a separate component using ng-content, the child directives are not fetched in the grid.component.ts file.

**Expected Behavior:**

The child directives should be fetched correctly in the grid.component.ts file, regardless of whether e-columns are used directly in the ejs-grid tag or passed through ng-content.

**Actual Behavior:**

The child directives are not being fetched when e-columns are passed through ng-content in a separate component.

**Possible Solution:**

If you have any ideas for a potential fix, you can suggest them here.


### Minimal Reproduction

**Steps to Reproduce:**

1. Run the attached [sample](https://drive.google.com/file/d/19yDSLzTxXf6OyvMghMkkyZGESzKshTIK/view),
2. Debugg the our angular grid component source,
3. In the grid component source, you can't get the childColumns value in the ngAfterContentChecked() hook.

